Hyundai to Build $167-Million Algeria Crude Gathering Plant

-- B y   S a l a h   S l i m a n i
-- 
2011-09-08T16:16:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-08/hyundai-to-build-167-million-algeria-crude-gathering-plant.html
Hyundai Group  won a $167-million
contract to build a crude-gathering plant at the Bir El M’Sana
oilfield in southern Algeria, according to state-run energy
company Sonatrach.  The contract was signed by Sonatrach, Hess Corp. and
 Malaysia ’s Petroliam Nasional Bhd., known as Petronas, Sonatrach
said in a statement distributed to reporters in Algiers.  The plant, which will have a capacity to handle 13,200
barrels a day of crude, is scheduled to be completed in 30
months with production starting in April 2014, the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Salah Slimani at 
 sslimani2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
